Package: countMissing
Title: Count Missing Values For All Columns By Group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Yasmine", "McDonough", , "yazzi@student.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`,
    `count_all_missing_by_group()` creates a new data frame with one row
    per level of `group`. The first column of the output data frame
    contains the levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain
    the number of missing values for all columns in `data` except `group`.
